===Buddhist countries===
Governments where [[Buddhism]], either a specific form of, or the whole, has been established as an official religion:

====Theravada Buddhism====
* {{Flag|Cambodia}}<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.cambodia.org/facts/?government=The+Constitution+of+Cambodia |title=Constitution of Cambodia |publisher=cambodia.org |accessdate=2011-04-13 |postscript=.}} (Article 43).</ref>
* {{Flag|Sri Lanka}}: the [[constitution of Sri Lanka]] accords Buddhism the "foremost place", although it does not identify it as a state religion.<ref>{{cite book|url=http://www.priu.gov.lk/Cons/1978Constitution/ |title=The Constitution of the Republic of Sri Lanka |chapter=Chapter II — Buddhism |chapter-url=http://www.priu.gov.lk/Cons/1978Constitution/Chapter_02_Amd.html |publisher=The Official Website of the Government of Sri Lanka |accessdate=2007-10-18 |postscript=. |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20090116183038/http://www.priu.gov.lk/Cons/1978Constitution/ |archivedate=16 January 2009 }}fv</ref>
* {{Flag|Myanmar}}: Section 361 of the constitution states that "The Union recognizes special position of Buddhism as the faith professed by the great majority of the citizens of the Union.".<ref>{{Cite web|title = Constitution of the Republic of the Union of Myanmar, Section 361: Buddhism as Majority Religion|url = http://berkleycenter.georgetown.edu/quotes/constitution-of-the-republic-of-the-union-of-myanmar-section-361-buddhism-as-majority-religion|website = berkleycenter.georgetown.edu|accessdate = 2015-11-22}}</ref>

